<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>point of no return • turning point</xh5><p> <i>point of no return—</i>the point beyond which one must continue on his current course of action, because turning back would be too expensive or dangerous: We have finally reached the <u>point of no return</u> where the drums for peace are now louder than the drums for war.</p><p> <i>turning point—</i>a decisive moment at which a very significant change for better or worse occurs: The Chernobyl disaster was a <u>turning point</u> for the nuclear power worldwide. It demonstrated that nuclear power in parts of the world was not safe enough.</p> </entry>
